    "status" : "<code>", // R! draft | active | retired | unknown
// source[x]: Identifies the source of the concepts which are being mapped. One of these 2:
    "sourceUri" : "<uri>", // R! Identifies the source of the concepts which are being mapped
    "sourceCanonical" : "<canonical>", // R! Identifies the source of the concepts which are being mapped
// target[x]: Provides context to the mappings. One of these 2:
    "targetUri" : "<uri>", // R! Provides context to the mappings
    "targetCanonical" : "<canonical>" // R! Provides context to the mappings
    "group" : [{ // C? R! Only One!  Same source and target systems
      "extension": [
      ],
      "element" : [{ // C? R! Mappings for a Vendor Analyte Code from the source set
        "extension": [
        ],
        "code" : "<code>", // R! Identifies the Vendor Analyte Code being mapped
        "display" : "<string>", // R! The Vendor Analyte Name
        "target" : [{ // C? Identifies the LOINC code being mapped to
          "extension": [
          ],
          "code" : "<code>", // R! Code that identifies the LOINC Code
          "display" : "<string>", // R! LOINC Long Name
          "equivalence" : "<code>", // R! relatedto | equivalent | equal | wider | subsumes | narrower | specializes | inexact | unmatched | disjoint
          "comment" : "<string>", // Vendor Comment
          "dependsOn" : [{ // C? R! Other elements required for this mapping (from context)
            "extension": [
            ],

          }],
        }],
      }],
    }],
  }
